		{
			title: "Crystal Growth Accelerator"
			icon: "appliedenergistics2:quartz_growth_accelerator"
			x: 15.5d
			y: 7.0d
			shape: "gear"
			subtitle: "Make em grow faster already! Left Click for more info"
			description: [
				"Growing those damn crystals usually takes around 20 minutes. Since you cannot go around wasting so much time, here's a way of growing them faster. We are pleased to present to you The Crystal Growth Accelerator."
				""
				"Things are simple. The more of these you use, the faster the growing process will be. You can use a maximum amount of 5 for one setup and each one of them will speed up the growing process."
				""
				"Each one of them has to be provided with power (they can accept it only through the top/buttom) and here's an example of how a basic setup looks like:"
				""
				"{image:kubejs:textures/ae2/crystal_growth_accelerator_example.png width:100 height:100 align:1}"
				""
				"Keep in mind that you'll have to supply the power for the Accelerators through the Energy Acceptor, otherwise things will not work!"
				""
				"Lastly, here's a chart of how each added Accelerator affects the growth time:"
				""
				"- None: 20 minutes"
				"- 1: 2 minutes"
				"- 2: 1 minute"
				"- 3: 40 seconds"
				"- 4: 30 seconds"
				"- 5: 24 seconds"
			]
			dependencies: ["02FD2E2781CA26DB"]
			id: "7B59D3A24CC98569"
			tasks: [{
				id: "3F0FFBE48AD2E10A"
				type: "item"
				item: "appliedenergistics2:quartz_growth_accelerator"
			}]
			rewards: [{
				id: "2EC206C12BA221B5"
				type: "item"
				item: "appliedenergistics2:fluix_glass_cable"
				count: 32
			}]
		}
		{
			title: "Making Pure Quartz Crystals"
			x: 11.0d
			y: 9.5d
			shape: "square"
			subtitle: "Well, you can't just use regular Fluix Crystals in these machines, right? You have to use Pure ones, of course <3 Left Click for more info"
			description: [
				"The Machines you're about the make are added by Applied Energistics 2 and, in this pack, they require Pure Fluix Crystals. If you're familiar with AE2 you know that there are two ways you can get Pure Fluix Crystals."
				""
				"One is to just throw them in a pond of Water, have them sorrounded by powered Crystal Growth Accelerators and wait a few minutes for them to grow. Well, this is the advanced way and you'll have access to it later, but not right now."
				""
				"Ok, then what's the 2nd way? You can just throw them in a regular Water pond and wait. It takes 12 IRL hours for them to grow so make sur-"
				""
				"\"You guys are ok, right?\""
				""
				"Alright, alright, there's a 3rd way. By placing one seed in a Crystal Growth Unit, you'll be able to get 8 Pure Crystals in about 20 IRL minutes. While you can get a lot of Crystals this way, it takes a lot of time to obtain them and it also requires some power. So, you'll most probably be interested in some Crystal Growth Accelerators as they're much more faster and they require less power."
				""
				"Oh, also the Growth Unit cannot be upgraded."
			]
			dependencies: ["17036C35C69172CC"]
			dependency_requirement: "all_started"
			id: "620CBC910FEB2996"
			tasks: [
				{
					id: "0C8166477EE9FB74"
					type: "item"
					item: {
						id: "custommachinery:custom_machine_item"
						Count: 1b
						tag: {
							machine: "custommachinery:crystal_growth_unit"
						}
					}
				}
				{
					id: "4470F9D193C5095E"
					type: "item"
					item: "appliedenergistics2:purified_fluix_crystal"
				}
			]
			rewards: [{
				id: "11A3100E49755E49"
				type: "item"
				item: "appliedenergistics2:purified_nether_quartz_crystal"
				count: 64
			}]
		}
		{
			title: "The Inscriber"
			x: 11.0d
			y: 8.5d
			shape: "square"
			subtitle: "The \"I hate automation\" Machine. Left Click for more info"
			description: [
				"The inscriber is used to press items using various Inscriber Plates. Each operation requires 1k RF/FE/AE charged up."
				""
				"Its main use will be for crafting advanced processors which will later be used in many recipes around Ae2 and beyond."
				""
				"It will be quite unfortunate to tell you that automating this machine will be quite hard. It can be fully automated using storage buses and various other means, but for now you'll be able to semi-automate it using hoppers. Use the fact that specific sides of the inscriber insert into specific slots to your advantage."
				""
				"Here's how specific sides of the machine interact with its slots:"
				""
				"- Top Input: Top Side"
				"- Center Input: Middle Sides"
				"- Bottom Input: Bottom Side"
				"- Output: Middle Sides"
				""
				"Note that the inscribers can (and should) be rotated 90 degrees with a wrench to fully take advantage of this feature."
			]
			dependencies: [
				"620CBC910FEB2996"
				"707659BED60BED08"
			]
			id: "7085ED71734DBE6C"
