		{
			x: 14.0d
			y: 7.0d
			shape: "square"
			subtitle: "Because Applied Energistics 2 uses AE instead of RF! Left Click for more info"
			description: [
				"Just like any other tech mod, Ae2 needs power, too. While the most majority of tech mods use RF/FE, Ae2 uses AE. Oh, wait.. you're making only RF/FE right now. Well, no problem, you can convert this type of electricity into AE with ease through the use of an Energy Acceptor."
				""
				"This Transformer converts energy from external systems into AE and stores it in the ME Network. What's the ME Network? Glad you asked. That's what's comming next in the \"Storage - 3\" tab."
				""
				"Oh, forgot to tell you. 2 RF/FE = 1 AE. Do what you want with this information."
			]
			dependencies: ["4CF1DAD5B1DD93B0"]
			id: "02FD2E2781CA26DB"
			tasks: [{
				id: "04A7118BD9E3C2F4"
				type: "item"
